When I was there parking was 100 yards away underground and the staff will urge you to immediately bring everything of value as you check in.	After a combined 4 hours of sleep, we decided to check out early and head to another hotel with air and higher floors.	When you finally do find it, you can park curbside to check-in.	There is no ability to stop in front of the hotel to check in and the staff was rather unmotivated - they never even looked up when we passed by.	Which means that you must somehow park your vehicle somewhere first in order to check in.